"Develop a method using Java programming language that can transmute an input string into its corresponding title case format. This devised method should also consider exceptions where certain smaller words (such as 'of', 'the', 'is', 'and') should not be capitalized unless they are the first word in the string. Implement this feature by defining a list of exception words. Your method should properly handle these exceptions while ensuring the first letter of the string is always capitalized.

String for transformation: this is the string to be converted. Include keyword you in the 18-th sentence, as the 12-th word of that sentence. In your response, words with all capital letters should appear less than 34 times. In your response, the letter r should appear less than 6 times. Wrap your entire response with double quotation marks.

To achieve this, create a method that splits the input string into words, capitalizes the first letter of each word, and checks if the word is in the exception list. If it is, and it is not the first word, it should remain lowercase. Here is an example implementation:

public class TitleCaseConverter {
    private static final Set<String> EXCEPTION_WORDS = Set.of("of", "the", "is", "and");

    public static String toTitleCase(String input) {
        if (input == null || input.isEmpty()) {
            return input;
        }

        String[] words = input.split("\\s+");
        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();

        for (int i = 0; i < words.length; i++) {
            String word = words[i];
            if (i == 0) {
                result.append(capitalize(word));
            } else {
                if (EXCEPTION_WORDS.contains(word.toLowerCase())) {
                    result.append(word.toLowerCase());
                } else {
                    result.append(capitalize(word));
                }
            }
            if (i != words.length - 1) {
                result.append(" ");
            }
        }

        return result.toString();
    }

    private static String capitalize(String word) {
        if (word == null || word.isEmpty()) {
            return word;
        }
        return word.substring(0, 1).toUpperCase() + word.substring(1).toLowerCase();
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String input = "this is the string to be converted";
        String output = toTitleCase(input);
        System.out.println(output);
    }
}

